lume is edited by Nikhil Pal Singh and includes a lengthy introduction based on interviews he conducted with O'Dell on his early life and later experiences. Climbin' Jacob's Ladder provides readers with a firm grasp of the civil rights movement's left wing, which O'Dell represents, and illuminates a more radical and global account of twentieth-century US history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAfrican AmericansxCivil rightsxHistoryy20th century. 0aAfrican AmericansxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aCivil rights movementszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a1940s.  a1950s.  a1960s.  a1980s.  a20th century.  aafrican americans.  aamerica.  aanti racist.  ablack freedom movement.  ablack freedom.  acivil rights movement.  acollected writings.  acommunist party.  ahistorical record.  ahistorical.  ahuman condition.  ainternational efforts.  aleft wing.  amartin luther king jr.  anational maritime union.  anonfiction.  apolitical.  aradical politics.  arainbow coalition.  ared baiting.  aretrospective.  asocial justice.  aunited states.  aunsung heroes.  aus history.1 aSingh, Nikhil Pal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSingh, Nikhil Pal, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025958440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094506740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945067423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520945067/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY